metatags.title: Conspiracy Theorists Claim Katy Perry is Actually JonBenet Ramsey, Even Though She's Obviously Not
metatags.body:
Is Katy Perry actually the late JonBenét Ramsey grown up? Very simply, no. But that hasn't stopped conspiracy theorists from thinking it's so and posting videos defending the opinion online. 
Katy Perry Invited Taylor Swift to Her Pre-Grammy Party
A few videos -- most made more than a year ago -- have been making the rounds widely, stating that the pop star is actually the pageant princess grownup. The videos that the Ramsey saga, where a 6-year-old girl was struck on the head and strangled to death in her home, ?was all a hoax orchestrated by the Illuminati and Free Masons to make money and make Perry a star.
The conspiracists cite everything from Perry's lyrics, tweets and music videos as proof, as well as a physical resemblance between Perry and Ramsey's parents. Similarities in their wardrobes are brought to question and in one video a man even claims that Perry and Ramsey's eyebrows are proof that they are the same person.

The Internet is abuzz about claims that the 1996 murder case is actually a hoax.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The Internet is abuzz with  claiming that JonBonet Ramsey's unsolved 1996 murder was all a ruse.
In a resurfaced YouTube video from December 2014, a man named Dave Johnson claims that Ramsey is not dead but is in fact . Johnson, who does not show his face in the video, claims the family kept this secret so that Perry could rise to fame.
****
"All of these people are liars, man," he says over images of Perry and Ramsey. "Nobody died, nobody got hurt. That sacrifice was in name only, and that was to get something, and that something was to become a star. JonBenet became Katy Perry, and that’s a fact."
Johnson even compares the singer's parents, pastors Keith Hudson and Mary Perry, to the Ramseys. This all despite the fact that Patsy Ramsey died in June 2006 of ovarian cancer. John Ramsey was remarried in 2011 to fashion designer Jan Rousseaux.
"He shaved his head, she lost some weight," Johnson alleges as he compares photos of the parents.
****
Another hole in this conspiracy theory is the age difference of Perry and Ramsey. The musician is 31, while Ramsey would only be 25 if she were alive today.
Still, YouTube , says you can tell these two are the same person because of their similar eyebrows. "You know, the eyebrows don’t change much...[Content truncated]

 has finally responded to one of the most twisted conspiracy theories of our time — well, sort of.
While hosting MTV's VMAs 2017, one of Katy's pre-recorded videos featuring Billy Eichner played during a transition. In true _Billy on the Street_ fashion, the comedian asked Katy a string of rapid-fire questions. And one of them happened to be about whether or not the "Swish Swish" singer is .
"Blink twice if you're actually JonBenet Ramsey," he asks. Billy's, of course, referring back to a  that went viral in early 2016. It alleges that JonBenet did not actually die back in 1996 and instead became who we now know today as Katy Perry. There are plenty of holes in the flimsy theory, but it being just wacky enough paired with the two looking somewhat similar made for good internet kindling.

website_content.content:
[Content truncated]...=================================================================
**Photo: Photo: Randall Simons/Polaris.**
I can remember a period in the mid-'90s when my mom forbade me from looking at the magazines in the grocery store checkout. They were plastered with pictures of a little girl around my age, whose bright blue eyes and bouncy blonde curls were so perfectly doll-like that at first glance she didn't seem to be real. But JonBenét Ramsey's face is the kind that sticks in your mind. She was a radiant, beautiful child — that's one reason people still remember her. Another one: her tragic murder, which has remained unsolved for nearly 20 years. Conspiracy theorists, not to mention actual detectives, are still stuck on decoding clues that would finally break her case. Now, a video making the rounds suggests that JonBenét has been alive all along — and living her life undercover as the singer Katy Perry, no less. The theory is not only insane, it's highly offensive to the Ramsey family after everything they've been through. In 2014, YouTube user Dave Johnson  in which he claims, via voice-over, that Ramsey is living undercover as Katy Perry. "Nobody died, nobody got hurt. That sacrifice was in name only, and that was to get something, and that something was to become a star," he says. "JonBenét became Katy Perry, and that’s a fact.” The video suggests that Perry's parents are actually Patsy and John Ramsey in disguise as Keith Hudson and Mary Perry. "He shaved his head. She lost some weight," Johnson explains, as though that's enough evidence to prove that four distinct people are, in actuality, two skillful pretenders who have been keeping up a decades-long charade. (Patsy Ramsey, a former beauty queen herself, died in 2006; her ex-husband, John, has since remarried. Katy Perry's parents are both alive and  in their daughter's life.) The problem here isn't Johnson's proof or lack thereof: The video is inarguably invalid, and no one is entertaining the idea that there's any truth to it. What's fucked up is that — _even though we all know there isn't a kernel of truth in the theory_ — it's still making the rounds on the internet, where people are suddenly comparing a dead child's features with those of a 31-year-old pop singer.

That Katy Perry Is JonBenet Ramsey In Disguise
----------------------------------------------
Jamie McCarthy/Getty Images; Investigation Discovery/ABC
In early 2016, corners of the internet latched onto the idea that pop star Katy Perry was not, in fact, born Katheryn Elizabeth Hudson of Santa Barbara, California, but rather JonBenet Ramsey of Atlanta, Georgia. A YouTuber  in which he claimed that the late Ramsey, who was killed in 1996 at the age of 6, was still alive and touring the world under the pseudonym of Katy Perry, saying, "JonBenét became Katy Perry, and that's a fact." Despite this claimed "fact," it is, however, false that Perry is Ramsey.
That Avril Lavigne Died and Is Being Impersonated By a Double
-------------------------------------------------------------
Kristy Sparow/WireImage
A bizarre internet conspiracy theory about Avril Lavigne emerged in the past few years. While most fans of the Canadian artist understand that Lavigne took a few years off in the late 2000s and has tried out different looks and musical styles in the years since, certain pop rockers believe that the "Sk8er Boi" singer died in 2003, only to be replaced by an actress who continued Lavigne's career with the release of _Goodbye Lullaby_ (2011) and _Avril Lavigne_ (2013). The two albums were actually released by the real Lavigne, who is still alive.
That Tupac Is Still Alive and Living in Cuba
--------------------------------------------
Ron Galella/WireImage
Fans mourned the loss of Tupac Shakur in September 1996, after the beloved artist was shot and killed in Las Vegas. Some supporters, however, were less than convinced.  about the nature of the violence and the handling of the case, and fans periodically report spotting Tupac in Cuba or in photos taken after his death. While conspiracies abound about the death of the icon, there is no real evidence that he is living in Cuba.

These days, you can seemingly find a conspiracy theory for anything on the Internet. For example, according to people on the web, Beyoncé was never actually pregnant, Chris Brown never attacked Rihanna and Nicki Minaj is actually Jay Z. But the latest piece of speculation making its way around the web is especially bizarre: JonBenét Ramsey, the child pageant queen who was murdered in 1996, grew up to be pop princess Katy Perry.
The Kernel took a deep dive into the wacky world of this theory. If bizarre long reads about the entertainment industry's dark secrets are your thing, it's definitely worth a read. But for your easy reading pleasure, we've compiled the most ~telling~ points below.
